<br>
So, what I suggest is that you heed the advice other folks have provided and forget about Mana Burn UNLESS you can manage to justify using it because of your UBER Mana Regen.<br>
<br>
Here are just a few things that can boost your Mana regeneration to lessen the effect of starting a fight with Zero mana -<br>
<br>
Get a Mod Rod<br>
<br>
Group with Shadow Knights and/or Necromancers and beg them to use their group mana replenish taps.<br>
<br>
Stand next to the Bard that is singing Mana Song or whatever<br>
<br>
Get a Mana Robe / Free right click nuke item<br>
<br>
Get Flowing Thought gear<br>
<br>
Train the AA ability Harvest of Druzzil and save it for after the burn<br>
<br>
Memorize the Harvest spell and save it for after the burn<br>
<br>
Train Mental Clarity 3 (Oh wait, this is a prerequisite anyways, nevermind)<br>
<br>
Get Buffed with Voice of Quellious, BoT9, Force Shield, and Spiritual BeastLordbuffiness<br>
<br>
Get a Horse or Drogmor<br>
<br>
In fights where I use Mana Burn I can regenerate enough mana to nuke as I would normally before the mob dies.  It all comes down to whether or not your raid party has sufficient DPS as a WHOLE to kill the mob before you go OoM.  <br>
<br>
Obviously, this isn't something to do unless <br>
<br>
A) the mob is a gimpy add and you will have adequete downtime after killing it to regain mana<br>
<br>
or <br>
<br>
B) You have good focus gear, efficient nukes, and great Mana regen that allows you to continue nuking after your Mana Burn for the duration of the fight.<br>
<br>
Mana Burn does suck compared to it's previous implementation, however, it is still useful if you have the means to maximize it's potential.  Sadly, the number of cases where this IS in fact a strong strategy to utilize are far less than they were pre-patch.<br>
<br>
To echo again the opinion of others - It isn't going to change anytime soon, ignore it or make the most of it, it's your choice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daniell1>daniell1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/03 11:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mana burn</span><hr size=1> Killed Tunare yesterday.  Used the following lineup of spells with ID4 bracelet, Jungle Spider Fur Cap, BoR:<br>
